missions.name: Apollo 11
missions.description: First successful manned Moon landing by NASA in 1969. Neil Armstrong became the first human to walk on the Moon.

missions.name: Voyager 1
missions.description: Launched in 1977, it's the farthest spacecraft from Earth and continues to send data from interstellar space.

missions.name: Voyager 2
missions.description: Twin of Voyager 1, it explored all four outer planets and now continues its journey through interstellar space.

missions.name: Mars Curiosity Rover
missions.description: NASA's rover that has been exploring Mars since 2012, analyzing climate and geology.

missions.name: James Webb Space Telescope
missions.description: Launched in 2021, JWST is NASAâ€™s next-gen space telescope offering unprecedented views of the early universe.

missions.name: Hubble Space Telescope
missions.description: Launched in 1990, Hubble has captured stunning images of distant galaxies, nebulae, and star clusters.

missions.name: Artemis I
missions.description: The first mission of NASA's Artemis program to return humans to the Moon, launched uncrewed in 2022.

missions.name: Perseverance Rover
missions.description: Landed on Mars in 2021 to search for signs of ancient life and collect samples for future return.
